<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>SwiftWallet Terms and Conditions</title>
    <style>
      body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background:#f3f6fb; margin:0; padding:40px; }
      .card { max-width:760px; margin:0 auto; background:#fff; padding:30px; border-radius:12px; box-shadow:0 6px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); }
      button { background:#0b6cff; color:#fff; border:none; cursor:pointer; padding:10px 16px; border-radius:8px; }
      .muted { color:#64748b; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Terms and Conditions</h2>
      <p class="muted">By using SwiftWallet, you agree to comply with BSP regulations, applicable KYC and AML policies, and our privacy notice.</p>
      <p>SwiftWallet provides payment collection and disbursement services for regulated merchants. You are responsible for the accuracy of submitted information, documents, and beneficiary details. SwiftWallet may suspend accounts for suspicious activity, missing documentation, or non-compliance with applicable laws.</p>
      <p>We process personal data in accordance with our privacy notice and only use it for onboarding, transaction monitoring, fraud prevention, and compliance reporting. All uploaded documents are encrypted in transit and at rest.</p>
      <form method="post" action="/terms/accept">
        <button type="submit">Accept and Continue</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
